pted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":9,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":40,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":65,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":78,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Roger de Bredwardine was born about 1250, in Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England, his father, Sir Walter de Bredwardine, was 21 and his mother, Maude Britt, was 17. He had at least 1 son with Alice de Longchamp."},"et":{"about 1250–":"umbes 1250–Surnud","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1252–1330":"1252–1330","1282–Male":"1282–Surnud","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1234–Female":"1234–Surnud","about 1250":"umbes 1250","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1234":"1234","1330":"1330","1230":"1230","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","1282":"1282","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England":"Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1250–":"noin 1250–Kuollut","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1252–1330":"1252–1330","1282–Male":"1282–Kuollut","1230–Male":"1230–Kuollut","1234–Female":"1234–Kuollut","about 1250":"noin 1250","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1234":"1234","1330":"1330","1230":"1230","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","1282":"1282","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England":"Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1250–":"environ 1250–Décédé","1250–Female":"1250–Décédée","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1252–1330":"1252–1330","1282–Male":"1282–Décédé","1230–Male":"1230–Décédé","1234–Female":"1234–Décédée","about 1250":"environ 1250","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1234":"1234","1330":"1330","1230":"1230","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","1282":"1282","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England":"Bredwardi